nidoran-m.dex_entry: The male Nidoran has developed muscles that freely move its ears in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon's notice.
nidoran-m.name: nidoran-m

nidoran-f.dex_entry: Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.
nidoran-f.name: nidoran-f

nidorina.dex_entry: When it is with its friends or family, its barbs are tucked away to prevent injury. It appears to become nervous if separated from the others.
nidorina.name: nidorina

nidorino.dex_entry: Its horn is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.
nidorino.name: nidorino

nihilego.dex_entry: People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent. It is an Ultra Beast.
nihilego.name: nihilego

nincada.dex_entry: It makes its nest at the roots of a mighty tree. Using its whiskerlike antennae, it probes its surroundings in the pitch-black darkness of soil.
nincada.name: nincada

ninetales.dex_entry: It has long been said that each of the nine tails embody an enchanted power. A long-lived Ninetales will have fur that shines like gold.
ninetales.name: ninetales

ninetales-alola.dex_entry: It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.
ninetales-alola.name: ninetales-alola

ninjask.dex_entry: Because it darts about vigorously at high speed, it is very difficult to see. Hearing its distinctive cries for too long induces a headache.
ninjask.name: ninjask

noctowl.dex_entry: It unfailingly catches prey in darkness. Noctowl owe their success to superior vision that allows them to see in minimal light, and to their supple and silent wings.
noctowl.name: noctowl

noibat.dex_entry: They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
noibat.name: noibat

noivern.dex_entry: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.
noivern.name: noivern

nosepass.dex_entry: Its body emits a powerful magnetism. It feeds on prey that is pulled in by the force. Its magnetism is stronger in cold seasons.
nosepass.name: nosepass

numel.dex_entry: A Numel stores boiling magma in the hump on its back. It is a hardy Pokémon that can transport a 220-pound load. It has served humans at work since long ago.
numel.name: numel

nuzleaf.dex_entry: A forest-dwelling Pokémon that is skilled at climbing trees. Its long and pointed nose is its weak point. It loses power if the nose is gripped.
nuzleaf.name: nuzleaf

octillery.dex_entry: It ensnares its foe with its suction- cupped tentacles before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, it spews ink to escape.
octillery.name: octillery

oddish.dex_entry: This Pokémon grows by absorbing moonlight. During the daytime, it buries itself in the ground, leaving only its leaves exposed to avoid detection by its enemies.
oddish.name: oddish

omanyte.dex_entry: One of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by humans. If attacked, it withdraws into its hard shell.
omanyte.name: omanyte

omastar.dex_entry: An Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large, making its movements slow and ponderous.
omastar.name: omastar

onix.dex_entry: There is a magnet in its brain that prevents an Onix from losing direction while tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes steadily rounder and smoother.
onix.name: onix

oranguru.dex_entry: Known for its intelligence, this Pokémon looks down on inexperienced Trainers, so it's best for veteran Trainers.
oranguru.name: oranguru

oricorio.dex_entry: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in flames.
oricorio.name: oricorio

oshawott.dex_entry: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.
oshawott.name: oshawott

pachirisu.dex_entry: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
pachirisu.name: pachirisu

palkia.dex_entry: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
palkia.name: palkia

palossand.dex_entry: Buried beneath the castle are masses of bones from those whose vitality it has drained.
palossand.name: palossand

palpitoad.dex_entry: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.
palpitoad.name: palpitoad

pancham.dex_entry: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.
pancham.name: pancham

pangoro.dex_entry: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.
pangoro.name: pangoro

panpour.dex_entry: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.
panpour.name: panpour

pansage.dex_entry: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.
pansage.name: pansage

pansear.dex_entry: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600┬║ F.
pansear.name: pansear

paras.dex_entry: A Paras has parasitic tochukaso mushrooms growing on its back. They grow by drawing nutrients from the host. They are valued as a medicine for long life.
paras.name: paras

parasect.dex_entry: Parasect are known to infest the roots of large trees en masse and drain nutrients. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.
parasect.name: parasect

passimian.dex_entry: They form groups of about 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable - They will never let down a comrade.
passimian.name: passimian

patrat.dex_entry: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.
patrat.name: patrat

pawniard.dex_entry: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.
pawniard.name: pawniard

pelipper.dex_entry: It skims the tops of waves as it flies. When it spots prey, it uses its large beak to scoop up the victim with water. It protects its eggs in its beak.
pelipper.name: pelipper

persian.dex_entry: A Persian's six bold whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in its vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.
persian.name: persian

persian-alola.dex_entry: It looks down on everyone other than itself. Its preferred tactics are sucker punches and blindside attacks.
persian-alola.name: persian-alola

petilil.dex_entry: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.
petilil.name: petilil

phanpy.dex_entry: Phanpy's big ears serve as broad fans. When it becomes hot, it flaps the ears busily to cool down. Even the young are very strong.
phanpy.name: phanpy

phantump.dex_entry: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.
phantump.name: phantump

pheromosa.dex_entry: It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses uncleanness in this world. It is an Ultra Beast.
pheromosa.name: pheromosa

phione.dex_entry: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.
phione.name: phione

pichu.dex_entry: It is still inept at retaining electricity. When it is startled, it discharges power accidentally. It gets better at holding power as it grows older.
pichu.name: pichu

pidgeot.dex_entry: This Pokémon has gorgeous, glossy feathers. Many trainers are so captivated by the beautiful feathers on its head that they choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.
pidgeot.name: pidgeot

pidgeotto.dex_entry: This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its large territory. If its living space is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.
pidgeotto.name: pidgeotto

pidgey.dex_entry: It has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It can unerringly return home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.
pidgey.name: pidgey

pidove.dex_entry: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.
pidove.name: pidove

pignite.dex_entry: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.
pignite.name: pignite

pikachu.dex_entry: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.
pikachu.name: pikachu

pikipek.dex_entry: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and nesting.
pikipek.name: pikipek

piloswine.dex_entry: A Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair for enduring freezing cold. It uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.
piloswine.name: piloswine

pineco.dex_entry: A Pineco hangs from a tree branch and waits for prey. While eating, if it is disturbed by someone shaking its tree, it falls on the ground and suddenly explodes.
pineco.name: pineco

pinsir.dex_entry: Their pincers are strong enough to shatter thick logs. Because they dislike cold, Pinsir burrow and sleep under the ground on chilly nights.
pinsir.name: pinsir

piplup.dex_entry: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
piplup.name: piplup

plusle.dex_entry: It has the trait of cheering on its fellow Pokémon. By shorting out the electricity it releases from its paws, it creates pom-poms for cheering.
plusle.name: plusle

politoed.dex_entry: The curled hair on its head proves its status as a king. It is said that the longer and curlier the hair, the more respect it earns from its peers.
politoed.name: politoed

poliwag.dex_entry: It is possible to see this Pokémon's spiral innards right through its thin skin. However, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.
poliwag.name: poliwag

poliwhirl.dex_entry: Its body surface is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.
poliwhirl.name: poliwhirl

poliwrath.dex_entry: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
poliwrath.name: poliwrath

ponyta.dex_entry: A Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. Its legs become stronger as it stumbles and falls while trying to keep up with its parent.
ponyta.name: ponyta

poochyena.dex_entry: It savagely threatens foes with bared fangs. It chases after fleeing targets tenaciously. It turns tail and runs, however, if the foe strikes back.
poochyena.name: poochyena

popplio.dex_entry: This Pokémon snorts body fluid from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.
popplio.name: popplio

porygon.dex_entry: It is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data in order to enter cyberspace. A Porygon is copy- protected so it cannot be duplicated.
porygon.name: porygon

porygon2.dex_entry: It was created by humans using the power of science. It has been given artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.
porygon2.name: porygon2

porygon z.dex_entry: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.
porygon z.name: porygon z

primarina.dex_entry: It controls its water balloons by singing. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down a generation.
primarina.name: primarina

primeape.dex_entry: When it becomes furious, its blood circulation becomes more robust, and its muscles are made stronger. But it also becomes much less intelligent.
primeape.name: primeape

prinplup.dex_entry: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
prinplup.name: prinplup

probopass.dex_entry: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.
probopass.name: probopass

psyduck.dex_entry: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.
psyduck.name: psyduck

pumpkaboo.dex_entry: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.
pumpkaboo.name: pumpkaboo

pupitar.dex_entry: A Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it ejects under compression to propel itself like a jet. Its body can withstand a collision with solid steel.
pupitar.name: pupitar

purrloin.dex_entry: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.
purrloin.name: purrloin

purugly.dex_entry: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon's nest and claims it as its own.
purugly.name: purugly

pyroar.dex_entry: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the prideΓÇÖs cubs.
pyroar.name: pyroar

pyukumuku.dex_entry: It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.
pyukumuku.name: pyukumuku

quagsire.dex_entry: A Quagsire hunts by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in. Because it doesn't move, it does not get very hungry.
quagsire.name: quagsire

quilava.dex_entry: It intimidates foes with intense gusts of flames and superheated air. Its quick nimbleness lets it dodge attacks even while scorching an enemy.
quilava.name: quilava

quilladin.dex_entry: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.
quilladin.name: quilladin

qwilfish.dex_entry: A Qwilfish uses the pressure of water it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming to be somewhat challenging.
qwilfish.name: qwilfish

raichu.dex_entry: If it stores too much electricity, its behavior turns aggressive. To avoid this, it occasionally discharges excess energy and calms itself down.
raichu.name: raichu

raichu-alola.dex_entry: It uses psychokinesis to control electricity. It hops aboard its own tail, using psychic powers to lift it and move about.
raichu-alola.name: raichu-alola

raikou.dex_entry: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. Its roars send shock waves shuddering through the air and ground as if lightning bolts were crashing down.
raikou.name: raikou

ralts.dex_entry: A Ralts has the power to sense the emotions of people and Pokémon with the horns on its head. It takes cover if it senses any hostility.
ralts.name: ralts

rampardos.dex_entry: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.
rampardos.name: rampardos

rapidash.dex_entry: It usually canters casually in the fields and plains. But once a Rapidash turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.
rapidash.name: rapidash

raticate.dex_entry: A Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
raticate.name: raticate

raticate-alola.dex_entry: It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputs over food happen often.
raticate-alola.name: raticate-alola

rattata.dex_entry: A Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly moves its ears and listens for danger. It will make its nest anywhere.
rattata.name: rattata

rattata-alola.dex_entry: With its incisors, it gnaws through doors and infiltrates people's homes. Then it steals whatever food it finds.
rattata-alola.name: rattata-alola

rayquaza.dex_entry: A Pokémon that flies endlessly in the ozone layer. It is said it would descend to the ground if Kyogre and Groudon were to fight.
rayquaza.name: rayquaza

regice.dex_entry: Its entire body is made of Antarctic ice. After extensive studies, researchers believe the ice was formed during an ice age.
regice.name: regice

regigigas.dex_entry: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.
regigigas.name: regigigas

regirock.dex_entry: A Pokémon that is made entirely of rocks and boulders. If parts of its body chip off in battle, Regirock repairs itself by adding new rocks.
regirock.name: regirock

registeel.dex_entry: Its body is harder than any other kind of metal. The body metal is composed of a mysterious substance. Not only is it hard, it shrinks and stretches flexibly.
registeel.name: registeel

relicanth.dex_entry: A Pokémon that was once believed to have been extinct. The species has not changed its form for 100 million years. It walks on the seafloor using its pectoral fins.
relicanth.name: relicanth

remoraid.dex_entry: A Remoraid uses its abdominal muscles to forcefully expel swallowed water, then shoot down flying prey. When evolution approaches, it travels down rivers.
remoraid.name: remoraid

reshiram.dex_entry: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.
reshiram.name: reshiram

reuniclus.dex_entry: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.
reuniclus.name: reuniclus

rhydon.dex_entry: Its horn, which rotates like a drill, destroys tall buildings with one strike. It stands on its hind legs, and its brain is well developed.
rhydon.name: rhydon

rhyhorn.dex_entry: Once it starts running, it doesn't stop. Its tiny brain makes it so stupid that it can't remember why it started running in the first place.
rhyhorn.name: rhyhorn

rhyperior.dex_entry: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.
rhyperior.name: rhyperior

ribombee.dex_entry: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others for battle.
ribombee.name: ribombee

riolu.dex_entry: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.
riolu.name: riolu

rockruff.dex_entry: It's a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendlinless, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.
rockruff.name: rockruff

roggenrola.dex_entry: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.
roggenrola.name: roggenrola

roselia.dex_entry: A Roselia that drinks nutritionally rich springwater blooms with lovely flowers. The fragrance of its flowers has the effect of making its foes careless.
roselia.name: roselia

roserade.dex_entry: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.
roserade.name: roserade

rotom.dex_entry: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
rotom.name: rotom

rowlet.dex_entry: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.
rowlet.name: rowlet

rufflet.dex_entry: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.
rufflet.name: rufflet

sableye.dex_entry: It digs branching holes in caves using its sharp claws in search of food--raw gems. A Sableye lurks in darkness and is seen only rarely.
sableye.name: sableye

salamence.dex_entry: After many long years, its cellular structure underwent a sudden mutation to grow wings. When angered, it loses all thought and rampages out of control.
salamence.name: salamence

salandit.dex_entry: It burns its bodily fluids to create poisonous gas. It attack its enemies once they inhale it.
salandit.name: salandit

salazzle.dex_entry: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of perfumes.
salazzle.name: salazzle

samurott.dex_entry: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.
samurott.name: samurott

sandile.dex_entry: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.
sandile.name: sandile

sandshrew.dex_entry: When it curls up in a ball, it can make any attack bounce off harmlessly. Its hide has turned tough and solid as a result of living in the desert.
sandshrew.name: sandshrew

sandshrew-alola.dex_entry: It lives on snowy mountains. Its steel shell is very hard--so much so, it can't roll its body up into a ball.
sandshrew-alola.name: sandshrew-alola

sandslash.dex_entry: It curls up in a ball to protect itself from enemy attacks. It also curls up to prevent heatstroke during the daytime when temperatures rise sharply.
sandslash.name: sandslash

sandslash-alola.dex_entry: Fleeing a volcanic eruption, it settled on a snowy mountain. As it races through the snowfields, it sends up a spray of snow.
sandslash-alola.name: sandslash-alola

sandygast.dex_entry: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.
sandygast.name: sandygast

sawk.dex_entry: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.
sawk.name: sawk

sawsbuck.dex_entry: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.
sawsbuck.name: sawsbuck

scatterbug.dex_entry: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
scatterbug.name: scatterbug

sceptile.dex_entry: In the jungle, its power is without equal. This Pokémon carefully grows trees and plants. It regulates its body temperature by basking in sunlight.
sceptile.name: sceptile

scizor.dex_entry: A Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.
scizor.name: scizor

scolipede.dex_entry: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.
scolipede.name: scolipede

scrafty.dex_entry: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.
scrafty.name: scrafty

scraggy.dex_entry: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.
scraggy.name: scraggy

scyther.dex_entry: Its blindingly fast speed adds to the sharpness of its twin forearm scythes. The scythes can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.
scyther.name: scyther

seadra.dex_entry: The poisonous barbs all over its body are highly valued as ingredients for making traditional herbal medicine. It shows no mercy to anything approaching its nest.
seadra.name: seadra

seaking.dex_entry: It punches holes in boulders on stream- beds. This is a clever innovation that prevents its eggs from being attacked or washed away by the current.
seaking.name: seaking

sealeo.dex_entry: Sealeo live in herds on ice floes. Using its powerful flippers, it shatters ice. It dives into the sea to hunt prey five times a day.
sealeo.name: sealeo

seedot.dex_entry: It hangs off branches and absorbs nutrients. When it finishes eating, its body becomes so heavy that it drops to the ground with a thump.
seedot.name: seedot

seel.dex_entry: Seel hunt for prey in frigid, ice-covered seas. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.
seel.name: seel

seismitoad.dex_entry: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
seismitoad.name: seismitoad

sentret.dex_entry: They take turns standing guard when it is time to sleep. The sentry awakens the others if it senses danger. If one becomes separated, it turns sleepless with fear.
sentret.name: sentret

serperior.dex_entry: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents, but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.
serperior.name: serperior

servine.dex_entry: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.
servine.name: servine

seviper.dex_entry: Seviper and Zangoose are eternal rivals. It counters a Zangoose's dazzling agility with its swordlike tail, which also oozes a horrible poison.
seviper.name: seviper

sewaddle.dex_entry: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
sewaddle.name: sewaddle

sharpedo.dex_entry: The vicious and sly gangster of the sea. Its skin is specially textured to minimize drag in water. Its speed tops out at over 75 miles per hour.
sharpedo.name: sharpedo

shaymin.dex_entry: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.
shaymin.name: shaymin

shedinja.dex_entry: A peculiar Pokémon that floats in air even though its wings remain completely still. The inside of its body is hollow and utterly dark.
shedinja.name: shedinja

shelgon.dex_entry: It hardly eats while it awaits evolution. It becomes hardier by enduring hunger. Its shell peels off the instant it begins to evolve.
shelgon.name: shelgon

shellder.dex_entry: At night, it burrows a hole in the seafloor with its broad tongue to make a place to sleep. While asleep, it closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.
shellder.name: shellder

shellos.dex_entry: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.
shellos.name: shellos

shelmet.dex_entry: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.
shelmet.name: shelmet

shieldon.dex_entry: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.
shieldon.name: shieldon

shiftry.dex_entry: It is said to arrive on chilly, wintry winds. Feared from long ago as the guardian of forests, this Pokémon lives in a deep forest where people do not venture.
shiftry.name: shiftry

shiinotic.dex_entry: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People are confused by their lights and get lost.
shiinotic.name: shiinotic

shinx.dex_entry: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
shinx.name: shinx

shroomish.dex_entry: It loves to eat damp, composted soil in forests. If you enter a forest after a long rain, you can see many Shroomish feasting on composted soil.
shroomish.name: shroomish

shuckle.dex_entry: A Shuckle hides under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its shell while eating stored berries. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.
shuckle.name: shuckle

shuppet.dex_entry: This Pokémon roams about deep in the night seeking such negative emotions as grudges and envy. It retreats to its nest when the sun begins to rise.
shuppet.name: shuppet

sigilyph.dex_entry: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.
sigilyph.name: sigilyph

silcoon.dex_entry: It prepares for evolution using the energy it stored while it was a Wurmple. It keeps watch over the surroundings with its two eyes.
silcoon.name: silcoon

silvally.dex_entry: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type.
silvally.name: silvally

simipour.dex_entry: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
simipour.name: simipour

simisage.dex_entry: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
simisage.name: simisage

simisear.dex_entry: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
simisear.name: simisear

skarmory.dex_entry: A Pokémon that has a body and wings of steel. People in the past used feathers fallen from Skarmory to make swords and knives.
skarmory.name: skarmory

skiddo.dex_entry: Thought to be one of the first Pokemon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.
skiddo.name: skiddo

skiploom.dex_entry: It blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees F. Because its flower's blooming changes with the temperature, it is sometimes used as a thermometer.
skiploom.name: skiploom

skitty.dex_entry: A Skitty's adorably cute behavior makes it highly popular. In battle, it makes its tail puff out. It threatens foes with a sharp growl.
skitty.name: skitty

skorupi.dex_entry: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
skorupi.name: skorupi

skrelp.dex_entry: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.
skrelp.name: skrelp

skuntank.dex_entry: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
skuntank.name: skuntank

slaking.dex_entry: Hordes of Slaking gather around trees when fruits come into season. They wait around patiently for ripened fruits to fall out of the trees.
slaking.name: slaking

slakoth.dex_entry: It sleeps virtually all day and night long. It doesn't change its nest its entire life, but it sometimes travels great distances by swimming in rivers.
slakoth.name: slakoth

sliggoo.dex_entry: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.
sliggoo.name: sliggoo

slowbro.dex_entry: Its tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.
slowbro.name: slowbro

slowking.dex_entry: It undertakes research every day to solve the mysteries of the world. However, it apparently forgets everything if the Shellder on its head comes off.
slowking.name: slowking

slowpoke.dex_entry: It catches prey by dipping its tail in water at the side of a river. But it often forgets what it is doing and spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.
slowpoke.name: slowpoke

slugma.dex_entry: It is a species of Pokémon that lives in volcanic areas. If its body cools, its skin hardens and immobilizes it. To avoid that, it sleeps near magma.
slugma.name: slugma

slurpuff.dex_entry: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a humanΓÇÖs, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. ItΓÇÖs like it can see with its nose!
slurpuff.name: slurpuff

smeargle.dex_entry: A Smeargle marks its territory using a fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. About 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.
smeargle.name: smeargle

smoochum.dex_entry: It actively runs about, but also falls often. Whenever it falls, it will check its reflection on a lake's surface to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.
smoochum.name: smoochum

sneasel.dex_entry: A Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. It seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.
sneasel.name: sneasel

snivy.dex_entry: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
snivy.name: snivy

snorlax.dex_entry: Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its big belly as a place to play.
snorlax.name: snorlax

snorunt.dex_entry: They tend to move about in groups of around five Snorunt. In snowy regions, it is said that when they are seen late at night, snowfall will arrive by morning.
snorunt.name: snorunt

snover.dex_entry: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.
snover.name: snover

snubbull.dex_entry: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, it sends smaller Pokémon scurrying in terror. The Snubbull does seem a little sad at making its foes flee.
snubbull.name: snubbull

solgaleo.dex_entry: At activation of its third eye, it departs for another world where it is said to live.
solgaleo.name: solgaleo

solosis.dex_entry: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.
solosis.name: solosis

solrock.dex_entry: Solar energy is the source of this Pokémon's power. On sunny days, groups of Solrock line up facing the sun and absorb its light.
solrock.name: solrock

spearow.dex_entry: Its loud cry can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.
spearow.name: spearow

spewpa.dex_entry: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.
spewpa.name: spewpa

spheal.dex_entry: It is completely covered with plushy fur. As a result, it never feels the cold even when it is rolling about on ice floes or diving in the sea.
spheal.name: spheal

spinarak.dex_entry: The web it spins can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that a Spinarak determines its prey by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web.
spinarak.name: spinarak

spinda.dex_entry: It is distinguished by a pattern of spots that is always different. Its unsteady, tottering walk has the effect of fouling its foe's aim.
spinda.name: spinda

spiritomb.dex_entry: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
spiritomb.name: spiritomb

spoink.dex_entry: A Pokémon that manipulates psychic power at will. It doesn't stop bouncing even when it is asleep. It loves eating mushrooms that grow underground.
spoink.name: spoink

spritzee.dex_entry: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.
spritzee.name: spritzee

squirtle.dex_entry: Its shell is not just for protection. Its rounded shape and the grooves on its surface minimize resistance in water, enabling Squirtle to swim at high speeds.
squirtle.name: squirtle

stantler.dex_entry: Stantler's magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction.
stantler.name: stantler

staraptor.dex_entry: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.
staraptor.name: staraptor

staravia.dex_entry: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.
staravia.name: staravia

starly.dex_entry: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
starly.name: starly

starmie.dex_entry: People in ancient times imagined that Starmie were transformed from the reflections of stars that twinkled on gentle waves at night.
starmie.name: starmie

staryu.dex_entry: It gathers with others in the night and makes its red core glow on and off with the twinkling stars. It can regenerate limbs if they are severed from its body.
staryu.name: staryu

steelix.dex_entry: Steelix live even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core, reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
steelix.name: steelix

steenee.dex_entry: The sepals on its head are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.
steenee.name: steenee

stoutland.dex_entry: This extremely wise Pokémon excels at rescuing people stranded at sea or in the mountains.
stoutland.name: stoutland

stufful.dex_entry: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.
stufful.name: stufful

stunfisk.dex_entry: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of energy.
stunfisk.name: stunfisk

stunky.dex_entry: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.
stunky.name: stunky

sudowoodo.dex_entry: It mimics a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. But since its forelegs remain green throughout the year, it is easily identified as a fake in the winter.
sudowoodo.name: sudowoodo

suicune.dex_entry: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gliding elegance. It has the power to purify dirty water.
suicune.name: suicune

sunflora.dex_entry: Sunflora convert solar energy into nutrition. They are highly active in the warm daytime but suddenly stop moving as soon as the sun sets.
sunflora.name: sunflora

sunkern.dex_entry: Sunkern try to minimize movement to conserve the nutrients they have stored in their bodies for evolution. They will not eat, subsisting only on morning dew.
sunkern.name: sunkern

surskit.dex_entry: They gather on puddles after evening downpours, gliding across the surface of water as if sliding. It secretes honey with a sweet aroma from its head.
surskit.name: surskit

swablu.dex_entry: A Pokémon that has wings like cottony clouds. After enduring winter, in which little food is available, Swablu flocks move closer to towns in the spring.
swablu.name: swablu

swadloon.dex_entry: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
swadloon.name: swadloon

swalot.dex_entry: Its powerful stomach acid is capable of digesting almost anything. The one thing in the whole world a Swalot can't digest is its own stomach.
swalot.name: swalot

swampert.dex_entry: If it senses the approach of a storm and a tidal wave, it protects its seaside nest by piling up boulders. It swims as fast as a jet ski.
swampert.name: swampert

swanna.dex_entry: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.
swanna.name: swanna

swellow.dex_entry: A Swellow dives upon prey from far above. It never misses its targets. It takes to the skies in search of lands with a warm climate.
swellow.name: swellow

swinub.dex_entry: It roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under dried grass. It occasionally roots out hot springs.
swinub.name: swinub

swirlix.dex_entry: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and as sticky as cotton candy.
swirlix.name: swirlix

swoobat.dex_entry: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.
swoobat.name: swoobat

sylveon.dex_entry: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
sylveon.name: sylveon

taillow.dex_entry: Although it is small, it is very courageous. It will take on a larger Skarmory on an equal footing. However, its will weakens if it becomes hungry.
taillow.name: taillow

talonflame.dex_entry: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.
talonflame.name: talonflame

tangela.dex_entry: Its vines snap off easily and painlessly if they are grabbed, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by new growth the very next day.
tangela.name: tangela

tangrowth.dex_entry: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
tangrowth.name: tangrowth

tapu bulu.dex_entry: This guardian deity of Ula'ula is lazy. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then hits them with its horns.
tapu bulu.name: tapu bulu

tapu fini.dex_entry: This guardian deity of Poni controls water. They say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.
tapu fini.name: tapu fini

tapu koko.dex_entry: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning.
tapu koko.name: tapu koko

tapu lele.dex_entry: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.
tapu lele.name: tapu lele

tauros.dex_entry: It is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.
tauros.name: tauros

teddiursa.dex_entry: It licks its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. A Teddiursa makes its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.
teddiursa.name: teddiursa

tentacool.dex_entry: Its body is almost entirely composed of water. It ensnares its foe with its two long tentacles, then stabs with the poison stingers at their tips.
tentacool.name: tentacool

tentacruel.dex_entry: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.
tentacruel.name: tentacruel

tepig.dex_entry: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.
tepig.name: tepig

terrakion.dex_entry: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
terrakion.name: terrakion

throh.dex_entry: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.
throh.name: throh

thundurus.dex_entry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
thundurus.name: thundurus

timburr.dex_entry: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.
timburr.name: timburr

tirtouga.dex_entry: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.
tirtouga.name: tirtouga

togedemaru.dex_entry: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy.
togedemaru.name: togedemaru

togekiss.dex_entry: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.
togekiss.name: togekiss

togepi.dex_entry: As its energy, it uses the feelings of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. It stores up happy feelings in its shell, then shares them out.
togepi.name: togepi

togetic.dex_entry: It is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When it spots someone who is pure of heart, a Togetic appears and shares its happiness with that person.
togetic.name: togetic

torchic.dex_entry: If attacked, it strikes back by spitting balls of fire it forms in its stomach. A Torchic dislikes darkness because it can't see its surroundings.
torchic.name: torchic

torkoal.dex_entry: It battles using energy it gets from burning coal. When loosing smoke from its nostrils, it lets off a sound that is similar to a locomotive's horn.
torkoal.name: torkoal

tornadus.dex_entry: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.
tornadus.name: tornadus

torracat.dex_entry: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.
torracat.name: torracat

torterra.dex_entry: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
torterra.name: torterra

totodile.dex_entry: Despite its small body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While it may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough strength to cause serious injury.
totodile.name: totodile

toucannon.dex_entry: When it battles its beak heats up. The heat can easily exceed 100 degrees Celcius, causing severe burns when it hits.
toucannon.name: toucannon

toxapex.dex_entry: It crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.
toxapex.name: toxapex

toxicroak.dex_entry: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
toxicroak.name: toxicroak

tranquill.dex_entry: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
tranquill.name: tranquill

trapinch.dex_entry: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.
trapinch.name: trapinch

treecko.dex_entry: It makes its nest in a giant tree in the forest. It ferociously guards against anything nearing its territory. It is said to be the protector of the forest's trees.
treecko.name: treecko

trevenant.dex_entry: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.
trevenant.name: trevenant

tropius.dex_entry: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.
tropius.name: tropius

trubbish.dex_entry: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that crated this Pokémon.
trubbish.name: trubbish

trumbeak.dex_entry: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or Prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.
trumbeak.name: trumbeak

tsareena.dex_entry: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill.
tsareena.name: tsareena

turtonator.dex_entry: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.
turtonator.name: turtonator

turtwig.dex_entry: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.
turtwig.name: turtwig

tympole.dex_entry: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.
tympole.name: tympole

tynamo.dex_entry: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.
tynamo.name: tynamo

type: null.dex_entry: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.
type: null.name: type: null

typhlosion.dex_entry: It can hide behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intense flames. Typhlosion create blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.
typhlosion.name: typhlosion

tyranitar.dex_entry: A Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. It roams in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.
tyranitar.name: tyranitar

tyrantrum.dex_entry: Nothing could stop this Pokemon 100 years ago, so it behaved like a king.
tyrantrum.name: tyrantrum

tyrogue.dex_entry: Tyrogue become stressed out if they do not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the trainer must establish a regular training schedule.
tyrogue.name: tyrogue

tyrunt.dex_entry: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile It lived 100 million years ago.
tyrunt.name: tyrunt

umbreon.dex_entry: Umbreon evolved from exposure to the moon's energy pulses. It lurks in darkness and waits for its foes to move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.
umbreon.name: umbreon

unfezant.dex_entry: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
unfezant.name: unfezant

unown.dex_entry: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient text characters. Although research is ongoing, it is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown.
unown.name: unown

ursaring.dex_entry: In forests, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where an Ursaring gathers food. It walks through its forest collecting food every day.
ursaring.name: ursaring

uxie.dex_entry: Known as ΓÇ£The Being of Knowledge.ΓÇ¥ It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
uxie.name: uxie

vanillish.dex_entry: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.
vanillish.name: vanillish

vanillite.dex_entry: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.
vanillite.name: vanillite

vanilluxe.dex_entry: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.
vanilluxe.name: vanilluxe

vaporeon.dex_entry: Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow them to live underwater. They have the ability to freely control water.
vaporeon.name: vaporeon

venipede.dex_entry: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggresive.
venipede.name: venipede

venomoth.dex_entry: Venomoth are nocturnal--they only are active at night. Their favorite prey are insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.
venomoth.name: venomoth

venonat.dex_entry: Its coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body is said to have evolved for protection. Its large eyes never fail to spot even miniscule prey.
venonat.name: venonat

venusaur.dex_entry: Venusaur's flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.
venusaur.name: venusaur

vespiquen.dex_entry: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.
vespiquen.name: vespiquen

vibrava.dex_entry: It looses ultrasonic waves by rubbing its wings together. Since a Vibrava's wings are still in the process of growing, it can only fly short distances.
vibrava.name: vibrava

victini.dex_entry: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
victini.name: victini

victreebel.dex_entry: The long vine extending from its head is waved about as if it were a living thing to attract prey. When an unsuspecting victim approaches, it is swallowed whole.
victreebel.name: victreebel

vigoroth.dex_entry: It can't keep still because its blood boils with energy. It runs through the fields and mountains all day to calm itself. If it doesn't, it can't sleep at night.
vigoroth.name: vigoroth

vikavolt.dex_entry: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.
vikavolt.name: vikavolt

vileplume.dex_entry: In seasons when it produces more pollen, the air around a Vileplume turns yellow with the powder as it walks. The pollen is highly toxic and causes paralysis.
vileplume.name: vileplume

virizion.dex_entry: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
virizion.name: virizion

vivillon.dex_entry: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.
vivillon.name: vivillon

volbeat.dex_entry: With their taillights lit, Volbeat fly in a swarm, drawing geometric designs in the night sky. They move their nests if their pond water becomes dirty.
volbeat.name: volbeat

volcanion.dex_entry: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
volcanion.name: volcanion

volcarona.dex_entry: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
volcarona.name: volcarona

voltorb.dex_entry: It bears an uncanny and unexplained resemblance to a Poké Ball. Because it explodes at the slightest shock, even veteran trainers treat it with caution.
voltorb.name: voltorb

vullaby.dex_entry: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.
vullaby.name: vullaby

vulpix.dex_entry: It can freely control fire, making fiery orbs fly like will-o'-the-wisps. Just before evolution, its six tails grow hot as if on fire.
vulpix.name: vulpix

vulpix-alola.dex_entry: In hot weather, this Pokémon makes ice shards with its six tails and sprays them around to cool itself off.
vulpix-alola.name: vulpix-alola

wailmer.dex_entry: While this Pokémon usually lives in the sea, it can survive on land, although not too long. It loses vitality if its body becomes dried out.
wailmer.name: wailmer

wailord.dex_entry: It breathes through nostrils that it raises above the sea. By inhaling to its maximum capacity, a Wailord can dive close to 10,000 feet beneath the waves.
wailord.name: wailord

walrein.dex_entry: To protect its herd, the leader battles anything that invades its territory, even at the cost of its life. Its tusks may snap off in battle.
walrein.name: walrein

wartortle.dex_entry: Its large tail is covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness in battle.
wartortle.name: wartortle

watchog.dex_entry: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.
watchog.name: watchog

weavile.dex_entry: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
weavile.name: weavile

weedle.dex_entry: A Weedle has an extremely acute sense of smell. It distinguishes its favorite kinds of leaves from those it dislikes by sniffing with its big red proboscis (nose).
weedle.name: weedle

weepinbell.dex_entry: At night, a Weepinbell hangs on to a tree branch with its hooked rear and sleeps. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.
weepinbell.name: weepinbell

weezing.dex_entry: By diluting its toxic gases with a special process, the highest grade of perfume can be extracted. To Weezing, gases emanating from garbage are the ultimate feast.
weezing.name: weezing

whimsicott.dex_entry: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.
whimsicott.name: whimsicott

whirlipede.dex_entry: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.
whirlipede.name: whirlipede

whiscash.dex_entry: Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes. In the daytime, it sleeps in mud at the bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it continually feeds throughout the night.
whiscash.name: whiscash

whismur.dex_entry: Its cries equal a jet plane in volume. It inhales through its ear canals. Because of this system, it can cry continually without having to catch its breath.
whismur.name: whismur

wigglytuff.dex_entry: Its fur is the ultimate in luxuriousness. Sleeping alongside a Wigglytuff is simply divine. Its body expands seemingly without end when it inhales.
wigglytuff.name: wigglytuff

wimpod.dex_entry: As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leave a sparkling clean path in its wake.
wimpod.name: wimpod

wingull.dex_entry: It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it soars on updrafts.
wingull.name: wingull

wishiwashi.dex_entry: When in trouble, their eyes shine. The shining light attracts its comrades who will help them out.
wishiwashi.name: wishiwashi

wobbuffet.dex_entry: Usually docile, a Wobbuffet strikes back ferociously if its black tail is attacked. It makes its lair in caves where it waits for nightfall.
wobbuffet.name: wobbuffet

woobat.dex_entry: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.
woobat.name: woobat

wooper.dex_entry: Wooper usually live in water but come out onto land seeking food occasionally. On land, they coat their bodies with a gooey, toxic film.
wooper.name: wooper

wormadam.dex_entry: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.
wormadam.name: wormadam

wurmple.dex_entry: It sticks to tree branches and eats leaves. The thread it spits from its mouth, which becomes gooey when it touches air, slows the movement of its foes.
wurmple.name: wurmple

wynaut.dex_entry: A Wynaut loves to eat sweet fruits. It cleverly picks fruits using its earlike arms. They gather in fruit gardens, drawn by the fragrance.
wynaut.name: wynaut

xatu.dex_entry: It has the enigmatic power of foreseeing the future. Some people in different lands have long believed that Xatu are emissaries from another world.
xatu.name: xatu

xerneas.dex_entry: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
xerneas.name: xerneas

xurkitree.dex_entry: Because it raided a power plant, people think it energizes itself with electricity. It is an Ultra Beast.
xurkitree.name: xurkitree

yamask.dex_entry: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.
yamask.name: yamask

yanma.dex_entry: It can see 360 degrees without moving its eyes. It is a great flier capable of making sudden stops and turning midair to quickly chase down targeted prey.
yanma.name: yanma

yanmega.dex_entry: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.
yanmega.name: yanmega

yungoos.dex_entry: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustioni and falls asleep on the spot.
yungoos.name: yungoos

yveltal.dex_entry: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
yveltal.name: yveltal

zangoose.dex_entry: When it battles, it stands on its hind legs and attacks with its sharply clawed forelegs. Its fur bristles if it encounters any Seviper.
zangoose.name: zangoose

zapdos.dex_entry: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. It gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.
zapdos.name: zapdos

zebstrika.dex_entry: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it's angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.
zebstrika.name: zebstrika

zekrom.dex_entry: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.
zekrom.name: zekrom

zigzagoon.dex_entry: Rubbing its nose against the ground, it always wanders about back and forth in search of something. It is distinguished by the zigzag footprints it leaves.
zigzagoon.name: zigzagoon

zoroark.dex_entry: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
zoroark.name: zoroark

zorua.dex_entry: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
zorua.name: zorua

zubat.dex_entry: While living in pitch-black caverns, their eyes gradually grew shut and deprived them of vision. They use ultrasonic waves to detect obstacles.
zubat.name: zubat

zweilous.dex_entry: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.
zweilous.name: zweilous

zygarde.dex_entry: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even great power lies hidden within it.
zygarde.name: zygarde
